  "body": "### Description\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n_Type_: Bug\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n_Summary_: Screen \"Hold your card\" is shown even if card is touching the phone in case user changed PIN after 2 unsuccessful attempts. If move card away and hold it back it doesn't help, so user needs to clause app and launch it again in order to proceed using it.\n\n#### Expected behavior\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\nAfter PIN is changed screen Status Keycard (from profile) is shown\n\n#### Actual behavior\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\nHold your card screen is shown\n\n### Reproduction\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=1WCZRLcGi7UneJscK5s60u-O44KcI6jRP\n\n* Open Status and sign in with keycard\n* Open Profile -> Status Keycard -> Change PIN (from now on hold your card next to the phone)\n* Enter correct PIN, for new PIN enter different numbers so it't not valid (e.g 111333 and to confirm 111777). \n* After error PIN does not match repeat entering incorrect new PIN once more\n* on 3rd attempt to enter new PIN - enter correct numbers (e.g. 111333 and repeat same 111333), so PIN is changed\n* check what screen is shown after confirmation popup is closed\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n\n* Status version: 0.12.0 apk https://status-im-prs.ams3.digitaloceanspaces.com/StatusIm-190403-181003-8b6ae2-pr.apk\n\n#### Logs\nfull logcat: [wrongscreen.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/3042550/wrongscreen.log)\n\n",
